---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidenote from '../../components/Sidenote.astro';
import Sparkline from '../../components/Sparkline.astro';
---

<Base title="Behavioral Activation">
  <article>
    <h1>Behavioral Activation</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      Action first. Motivation follows. Not the other way around.
    </p>

    <h2>The Principle</h2>

    <p>
      Behavioral Activation (BA) comes from CBT research on depression: people who act
      <em>despite</em> not feeling motivated break the cycle faster than those who wait
      for motivation to arrive.
      <Sidenote id="research">
        Martell, Dimidjian, &amp; Herman-Dunn (2010). <em>Behavioral Activation for Depression.</em>
        Kanter et al. (2010) extended the framework to non-clinical productivity contexts.
      </Sidenote>
    </p>

    <p>
      For solopreneurs, this translates directly:
    </p>

    <pre><code>Traditional:  Motivation → Action → Result
BA approach:  Small Action → Result → Motivation → Bigger Action</code></pre>

    <h2>Applied to Daily Operations</h2>

    <h3>The 5-Minute Rule</h3>

    <p>
      If a task takes under 5 minutes, do it now. No list, no planning, no overthinking.
      The dashboard always shows at least one item completable in this window.
    </p>

    <h3>Activity Scheduling</h3>

    <p>
      BA uses <em>scheduled activities</em>, not infinite task lists.
      The dashboard shows exactly 5 items because:
    </p>

    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <li>5 is scannable in under 10 seconds</li>
      <li>At least one is completable in 5 minutes (guaranteed quick win)</li>
      <li>At least one is already done by an agent (progress without effort)</li>
      <li>Remaining items are pre-prioritized — no decision fatigue</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Avoidance Mapping</h3>

    <p>Common avoidance patterns for this project:</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Avoidance Behavior</th>
          <th>What I'm Actually Avoiding</th>
          <th>BA Response</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Reading Telegram/news</td>
          <td>Making a sales-related action</td>
          <td>Do the 5-min item first, <em>then</em> Telegram</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Coding a new skill</td>
          <td>Promoting existing skills</td>
          <td>Publish before building</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Researching tools</td>
          <td>Contacting a lead</td>
          <td>Send one message, then research</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Perfecting content</td>
          <td>Shipping imperfect content</td>
          <td>Ship today, improve tomorrow</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Reward Tracking</h3>

    <p>
      BA emphasizes tracking <em>actions taken</em>, not outcomes.
      <Sidenote id="tracking">
        Tracking actions (inputs) rather than results (outputs) reduces anxiety and
        maintains motivation even during slow sales periods. The streak itself becomes
        the reward.
      </Sidenote>
    </p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Metric</th><th>This Week</th><th>Trend</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Days with visibility action</td>
          <td>5/7</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[3, 4, 5, 4, 6, 5, 5]} type="bar" color="#059669" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Agent tasks reviewed</td>
          <td>12</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[5, 8, 7, 10, 9, 11, 12]} type="area" color="#2563eb" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Content pieces shipped</td>
          <td>3</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[1, 1, 2, 2, 1, 3, 3]} type="line" color="#d97706" /></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Connection to JTBD</h2>

    <p>
      The project's own job statement maps directly to BA:
    </p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Switch Force</th><th>BA Interpretation</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Push</strong> (morning confusion)</td><td>The avoidance cycle</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Pull</strong> (clear dashboard)</td><td>Scheduled activation</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Habit</strong> (Telegram/coding)</td><td>Avoidance behaviors</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Anxiety</strong> (task pile-up)</td><td>Solved by auto-archive + hard cap of 5</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </article>
</Base>
